==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manganous
<hw>Man"ga*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, designating, those compounds of manganese in
which the element has a lower valence as contrasted with
<contr>manganic</contr> compounds; <as>as, <ex>manganous</ex>
oxide</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Manganous acid</b></col>, <cd>a hypothetical compound
analogous to sulphurous acid, and forming the so-called
<xex>manganites</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mangcorn</ent>⟦br⟧
